Not everything goes as planned, but if I say I’m going to do something, I do it! Kids always come first, so better late then never, and honestly A LOT less crowded! 

@harleydavidson you have showed us the past, present and now future. Visiting the museum and seeing the roots that built our 2 wheel dreams, made us fall in love all over again! We are the future! 

For Justin and I, these trips keep us alive. Sometimes on 4 wheels to save time, with the bike behind, but with each state we go through, our bike gets a piece of American road and wind!

 (…and Justin not happy about loading everything back up again and again 😝)

REAL TALK - 10 years ago today I lost my dad after his 2nd heart attack - his first was after coming home from riding his Harley, I guess he wanted to make it memorable?

10 years ago I was lost. I had a 5 year old. I was divorced. I lost my best friend. I never thought anything would get better.

Anyone who who has lost a parent young knows it feels like you were robbed. What I have learned through out these years is that yes my heart will forever feel broken, but I was the luckiest girl in the world to have the Dad I did. Regardless of how long.

Continue to be grateful, remember it’s ok to feel sad sometimes, and live life to it’s fullest🧡🖤
.
